main event: A disc-shaped object, estimated to be the size of a planet, was sighted over the horizon at 33-39N 176-40W.
interesting points: The object appeared to be in orbit, and disappeared over the horizon from west to east.
The object's estimated velocity was twice that of a satellite.
The sighting occurred during daylight hours.
The object had the characteristics of a satellite, but no other details were given to identify it.
The observer was a high-flying recon jet (Echo) at 33,000 feet.
